- docker pull (name):version
- docker run name/id:(version) optional
- docker start name/id:(version)
- docker stop name/id:(version)
- docker image ..(to check the list of images we have in docker)
- docker ps ..(it will show the running continers )
- docker ps -a ...(it will show histroy of all the running containers)
- docker run -d name/id:(version)
- docker run -p (portno):(tpc port no or container port no) -d name/id (of image or continer)
- docker logs id/name (of the container)
- docker run -p 6000:6379 --name old redis:4.0 ///this is the example to set name along with port
- docker run -it node //The command docker run -it node creates and starts a new, interactive Docker container from the official node image, connecting your local terminal to the container's shell
- docker exec -it id/name (of the container) //this command will get me into the os of the continer itslef its getting into the the linux of the container
-docker network ls //lists all the docker networks..
-docker network create (name) //name of the network
